s articles====\n* {{cite magazine |last1=Reynolds |first1=Quentin |last2=Jones |first2=George E. |last3=Teatsorth |first3=Ralph |last4=Morris |first4=Frank D. |date=13 January 1945 |title=America's Greatest Naval Battle: Report on the Second Battle of the Philippines (First of three parts) |url=https://www.unz.com/print/Colliers-1945jan13-00011/ |pages=11\u201313, 64\u201365 |magazine=Collier's}}\n* {{cite magazine |last1=Reynolds |first1=Quentin |last2=Jones |first2=George E. |last3=Teatsorth |first3=Ralph |last4=Morris |first4=Frank D. |date=20 January 1945 |title=America's Greatest Naval Battle: Report on the Second Battle of the Philippines (Second of three parts) |url=https://www.unz.com/print/Colliers-1945jan20-00018/ |pages=18\u201319, 67\u201369 |magazine=Collier's}}\n* {{cite magazine |last1=Reynolds |first1=Quentin |last2=Jones |first2=George E. |last3=Teatsorth |first3=Ralph |last4=Morris |first4=Frank D. |date=27 January 1945 |title=America's Greatest Naval Battle: Report on the Second Battle of the Philippines (Third of three parts) |url=https://www.unz.com/print/Colliers-1945jan27-00018/ |pages=18, 69\u201372 |magazine=Collier's}}\n* {{cite magazine |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |magazine=Popular Mechanics |title=The Battle That Won the Pacific |volume=83 |issue=2 |date=February 1945 |url={{Google books |h98DAAAAMBAJ |p=17 |keywords=The Second Battle of the Philipine Sea|plain-url=yes}} |pages=17\u201325, 150 |issn=0032-4558 |publisher=Hearst Magazines}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons}}\n* [http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/AAF/USSBS/IJO/IJO-75.html United States Strategic Bombing Survey (Pacific) \u2013 Interrogations of Japanese Officials]\n* [http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/USN/rep/Leyte/BatExp/index.html Battle Experience: Battle for Leyte Gulf] [Cominch Secret Information Bulletin No. 22]\n* [http://ibiblio.org/hyperwar/USN/rep/Leyte/TF-34-Leyte.html Task Force 34 Action Report: 6 October 1944 \u2013 3 November 1944 (VAdm Lee)]\n* [h